%S A272002 2,0,7,8,6,1,4,9,5
%N A272002 Decimal expansion of Cp(1), the molar specific heat of an atomic ideal gas at constant pressure.
%C A272002 Also the decimal expansion of Cv(2), the molar specific heat of a diatomic gas at constant volume.
%C A272002 The molar specific heat of an n-atomic gas at constant pressure and volume can be calculated respectively with the following formulae:
%C A272002 - Cv(n) = (n + 1/2) R;
%C A272002 - Cp(n) = (n + 3/2) R;
%C A272002 Where R = Cp(n) - Cv(n) = A081822 is IUPAC's value of the gas constant.
%F A272002 Cp(1) = (1 + 3/2) * R = 5/2 * A081822.
%F A272002 Cp(1) = Cv(1) + R = A272001 + A081822.
%e A272002 Cp(1) = 20.7861495 J mol^-1 K^-1.
%Y A272002 Cf. A081822, A272001, A272003.
